{"_id":"EQLKQnYzB23Q9ROM","name":"Trott's Marauders","content":"<h1>FOR HIRE</h1>\n<h1>Trott's Marauders</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Victory at a Competitive Rate</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><img style=\"display:block;border:0px solid black;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"Images/Illustrations/Knight.png\" width=\"328\" height=\"352\" /></h3>\n<h1 style=\"text-align:center\">The Answer</h1>\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>to all your...</strong></h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Outstanding Territorial Claims</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Pretensions to Power</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Political Opposition</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Ungrateful Subjects</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Treacherous Relatives</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Noisy Neighbours</h3>\n<h1 style=\"text-align:center\">No Questions Asked!</h1>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">The Cost?</h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Very Reasonable</em></h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Ask for Lieutenant Vidar Skarost at the sign of the Slaughtered Orc.</h3>\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">Free Companies for hire include:</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Ulfug's Maneaters</strong> - 30 Ogre veterans</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Fullagar's Companions</strong> - 60 Freelance Knights</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>The Sabres of Glory</strong> - 80 Pistoliers</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Blackhand's Border Spears </strong>- 200 Spearmen</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>The Nuvala Company </strong>- 160 Tilean Pikemen</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Agbeiten Arbrustschutzen</strong> - 160 Crossbowmen</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>The Hellfire Twins</strong> - 2 Galloper Guns</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>The Dreaded Killers of Men </strong>- 40 Halflings</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align:center\">BOOK TODAY</h1>","img":null,"folder":"3D5AeQXPQFECRFtw","sort":1200001,"permission":{"default":2,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ESOE9gmdNHu11A1R","name":"BEZAHLTAG","content":"<h1 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">BEZAHLTAG</h1>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">The CRIMSON DARTS Flying Display</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">in the <strong>Great Park</strong> at the 3rd Hour after Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">SNOTBALL</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">in the <strong>Bernabau Stadium</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Eastenders vs Middenheim Carpenters</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">at the 3rd Hour after Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Southgate Slammers vs Beeckerhoven Rangers</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">at the 6th Hour after Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-6b70d8bf-7fff-6043-d0a5-9b86f85560fa\"></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>COME ON THE ’ENDERS !</strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align:center;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"> </p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">The Carroburg FIRE-BREATHERS</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">in the <strong>Bernabau Stadium</strong> from Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">ELVEN LIGHTSINGERS </h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">in the<strong> Royal College of Music </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">from the 3rd Hour after Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">In the <strong>Square of Martials:</strong></p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">ICE DANCING</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">from the 11th Hour before Noon</p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">EXHIBITION OF HERALDIC ARTS</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">from the 5th Hour after Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">Jade  Life Sculpting</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">in the <strong>Royal Gardens</strong> from the 2nd Hour after Noon</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\"> </p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">‘The Barbarian of Vesille’</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">at the <strong>Royal College of Music </strong></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:center\">at the 7th Hour after Noon</p>","folder":"LaUWtwaJi9qsofyf","sort":750000,"permission":{"default":2,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EWhez41BvMuwznUT","name":"NPC Strategy","content":"<p>Obviously, this depends on how much warning the pawns have, if they are asleep at the time, and so on. If they have already made an attack on the Characters they will be highly vigilant, and likewise, if the Characters have announced their presence by smashing down locked doors, they will be forewarned. These NPCs are fairly brave (save for @Actor[eeJoYIenRt8CbtVU]{Anton}): @Actor[b5sXx8PO9Jj8og2w]{Brunhilde} and @Actor[klwNbpAHe1oQ1oo6]{Dagmar} are unlikely to surrender, and @Actor[frMWa4mngN7z7n3g]{Hultz} will not do so unless offered amnesty. It is unlikely that any will be able to escape, although Brunhilde will try to get away to warn Wasmeier. Unfortunately, even if she does escape, Wasmeier will not be at home for most of Festag night, having other plans for the evening (see @JournalEntry[Vc09tZNuKQcfD7QP]{The Court Climax})</p>\n<h3>Advancing The Plotline</h3>\n<p>If the Characters discover the lair on Festag night, events are set to increase in pace. Assuming the love-letters have been found, the Characters should be able to guess who wrote them, and how politically sensitive they are. Even if they were unaware of the blackmail pressure on Ar-Ulric before, they should now understand why he has been silent on the tax issue. However, Reya Ehrlich is their biggest gain by far.  i. When ungagged, Reya will prove to be an independent and plucky sort, demanding to be taken to her uncle @Actor[2T8CXsP45Z3Kptvi]{Law Lord Ehrlich} — ‘he’ll know what to do!’ — or someone else in authority. In all probability, the Characters are quite unaware of the pressure exerted on @Actor[2T8CXsP45Z3Kptvi]{Law Lord Ehrlich}, and Reyas presence should be one more piece of the jigsaw.</p>\n<h4>Premature Annihilation</h4>\n<p>If the party deals with the pawns before Festag night, things change slightly. Reya Ehrlich is not in the lair. Instead of love-letters, the party finds a partly-burnt scrap of paper in the ashes close to the aviary. All that is readable (in code) is a place (of your choosing, in the @JournalEntry[NDbT1IWPeXXqHOlZ]{Altquartier}), and a time (11.30pm Festag night). This is where another group of cultists — or the Skaven, if they have not yet been encountered — hand over Reya and the love-letters to Klaglich. After that, events should continue as described above.</p>\n<p>If @Actor[b5sXx8PO9Jj8og2w]{Klaglich}  is killed, the first @Actor[lYEKyCpaihHON6Gz]{Wasmeier} knows about  it is when she fails to act on one of his messages, which may take time. He starts investigations using minor cultists, and if he discovers the lair has been attacked, he instructs a second group of cultists to take delivery of Reya and the letters. Since the original lair has been discovered, the cultists will plant the evidence in another run-down house. This meeting could get very complicated as both Characters and cultists wait for the same ‘shipment.’</p>\n<p>Finally, if @Actor[b5sXx8PO9Jj8og2w]{Klaglich} escapes an early attack, @Actor[lYEKyCpaihHON6Gz]{Wasmeier} will be warned immediately. Since neither of them knows that the Characters know of the handover on Festag night, there is no reason why the aforementioned delivery will not take place, but in this instance, it will be Klaglich waiting for the girl and letters, rather than other cultists. She  then plants the evidence as described in @JournalEntry[Vc09tZNuKQcfD7QP]{‘The Court Climax’}.</p>","folder":"8RbZHSArNQNSMvQ7","sort":200000,"permission":{"default":0,"nEodC92V8JiQPG6I":3,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e-pbtt":{"initialization-folder":"Chapter 7: The Traitor Unmasked","sort":200000}}}
{"_id":"EZ4xCAtOfYUytOOF","name":"Parravon","content":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c4bc547b-7fff-51b5-f2f8-1d8bb0a85283\"></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Starkly impressive</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Parravon lies upon the north bank of the upper Grismari, part of an outcropping of steeply rising chalk cliffs.</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Whitewashed walls and tall round turrets with fluttering pennants</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Many of the houses are cut into the rock face</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">The towering cliffs are home to thousands of birds whose white droppings pepper the red-tile roofs of this picturesque city.</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Can only be approached by a high arched bridge.</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">The river is narrow here, and the upper limit for large ships is at the city's northern edge, where small dockland warehouses are cut directly into the rugged rock.</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-19e44b6b-7fff-1942-5d12-6cb65460fca9\">Castle Parravon, seat of the Dukes, dominates the top of the outcrop with its soaring towers. </span></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Birds or something else circle the tall towers</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Castle Parravon</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Pegasus Eyries</li>\n<li>Hubert le Fauconnier</li>\n<li>Gardens</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Vue de Rocher</h3>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38\">Thindrongol: Secret vault in which ale or treasure is hidden</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Grail Chapel</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Actor[GEQJPAcYt2KCOjVw]{Ysabeau le Changeant - Damsel}</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Other Temples</h3>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Pere Jean-Pierre - High Priest of Morr</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">New Temple of Sigmar\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">Target of much ire</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a3d4d585-7fff-ec8b-a1a0-93cc5b237190\">The Parc St Gudule</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-20212ff5-7fff-42ce-1956-c960425f3153\">Reputed to be one of the best gardens in the Old World</span></li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d499f78a-7fff-7fd7-9c64-128e21051ed9\">Created in the 18th century IC by the famous ' Capacite' Doisneau: the greatest and most eccentric gardener ever to have lived.</span></li>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-816794b3-7fff-c1cf-9d38-390d3e786ab0\">Citizens brag that Doisneau so excelled himself with the labyrinth, which is said to get a little bit taller and more bristley every time someone gets a bit too lost and does not emerge</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>The Blackteeth</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Printing Houses</li>\n<li>Unofficial leader - Lucien Musset</li>\n<li>Halfling - Theodricus Wormfoot-Hulland</li>\n<li>Named for inked blocks</li>\n<li>Many speak Reikspiel</li>\n<li>Lots of Imperial Expats\n<ul>\n<li>Exiled from the Empire</li>\n<li>Allowed to print what they want by the Duc so long as they do not print anything bad about Bretonnia.</li>\n<li>@Actor[77SgLkjOO6pb7dE1]{Gilbert le Coq - Scholar}\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">L'Atelier du Coq</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\">Will give Bretonnian lessons</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Les Jacquards</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Actor[0t11kicw3rFYDVTq]{Reynard le Vif}</li>\n<li>The bird-training pickpocket</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-7e8da01b-7fff-1af6-b7c9-c3da26f6c6cf\"></span></p>\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">La Mesnée d'Hellequin</h3>\n<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-a9bfc921-7fff-8e4c-fc5c-f8eb096e99bf\"></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Arrive when Morrslieb is full</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Ride invisibly through the city blowing horns, howling dogs</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">The folk of Parravon bar doors and windows and huddle</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">Sometimes the Hellequins will take a peasant family</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">They do not bother with nobles</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">This has been going on for ~20 years</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Blind Nowl, the Seer of Parravon</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Blind Seer</li>\n<li>50 years ago took to eating strange fruit</li>\n<li>Bitter rich flavour, but a feast beyond compare</li>\n<li>Would make incredible alcohol</li>\n<li>Allowed Nowl to see spites</li>\n<li>One day he saw a cowled figure stealing a baby.</li>\n<li>He tried to stop it, but fell asleep</li>\n<li>When he awoke he was blind - to stop him from seeing the fey ever again.</li>\n<li>Charges 2 shillings for the story.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Roleplaying Notes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Use future tense when talking about the past.</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>“He’s got holes in his ankles”</em>: He can drink an enormous amount without showing any ill effects. People showing such ill effects sometimes decide to check for the holes.</p>\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3a651400-7fff-3bfe-2300-57243f94782d\"></span></li>\n<li>\n<p><em> “Duelling an avalanche”</em>: Utterly futile activity.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><em>“If you always look back, you never get home”</em>: Most things cannot be done in the obvious way. Or, look<br />to the future rather than the past.<span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"><span style=\"font-family:AGaramondPro-Italic;font-size:10pt;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:AGaramondPro-Regular;font-size:10pt;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:AGaramondPro-Italic;font-size:10pt;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal\"><br style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;line-height:normal;text-align:-webkit-auto;white-space:normal;text-size-adjust:auto\" /></span></span></span></span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">La Lune!</p>\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-53c67010-7fff-cfdf-48d7-303d26168f41\"></span></li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Désolé, je ne parle pas l' étranger, Monsieur. (Sorry, I don' t speak foreign, sir)</p>\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-53c67010-7fff-cfdf-48d7-303d26168f41\"></span></li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Quoi ? (What ?)</p>\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-53c67010-7fff-cfdf-48d7-303d26168f41\"></span></li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sacrebleu</p>\n</li>\n</ul>","folder":"hRh4ENgO4oLtD0If","sort":600001,"permission":{"default":0,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{}}
