{"_id":"Vm3hFYQ3tqoALTbL","name":"The Darkstone Ring","content":"<p>The wise do not venture to the Darkstone Ring. The path to this place of terrible and ancient power lies to the north of Blutroch the Altdorf-B&ouml;genhafen road. When night falls, the six suggestively-carved stones glow green with a wan luminosity, ﬂaring bright as Morrslieb waxes.</p>\n<p>At the center of the Darkstone Ring lies a monolithic slab of unidentifiable rock, permanently stained with the blood of the countless innocents sacrificed there down through the millennia.</p>\n<p>Despite the ring&rsquo;s fell reputation, travelers seem drawn to its malevolent environs, lured by legends of mystical potential and lost artefacts of terrible arcane power. Not even frequent sightings of beastmen and cultists &mdash; especially around Geheimnisnacht &mdash; can deter these brave, some may say foolhardy, souls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","folder":"iltPBXW0kOqlZhfA","sort":2100001,"permission":{"default":2,"rV2mzxh8yjNgvo3g":3,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e":{"initialization-folder":"Settlements"}}}
{"_id":"Vp6ZZV6dbUxG5Mot","name":"Additional Events","content":"<p>Argument between noble girl and urchins - resolve</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Tax confrontation</p>\n<p>Prunkvoll remains for whole party, main antagonist</p>\n<p>People who are pro taxes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rallane (leaves at 6:45)</li>\n<li>Dieter</li>\n<li>Ar-Ulric</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Schadelfaust turns up</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>+5SL Talfwick Gossip</p>\n<p>Taxes are fine and legit</p>","folder":"Rl69ySRItdzlcGbE","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"empire-divided","system":"wfrp4e","coreVersion":"9.280","systemVersion":"5.3.0"}}}
{"_id":"VxxxhuwPcTNmDCrI","name":"The Greenskin Hordes","content":"<p>Orcs and Goblins are the scourge of civilisation. They raid ceaselessly from their crude fortifications, most commonly warring amongst themselves, culling the weak and revering the strong. Inevitably, a Greenskin warlord will eventually arise from these internecine skirmishes and bind the neighbouring tribes under one banner. Then the drums of war sound, and the green tide swells once more, ready to wash over every village and town in its path, leaving nothing but blood and ruin in its wake. </p>\n<p>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.bestiary.E7BiDqsB55BrOQut]{Orc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.bestiary.zzdOpKqBC28J66Mn]{Goblin}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.bestiary.wdnXbjtKK7MtsZzc]{Snotling}</p>","folder":"iydq3xyNvZyEGeMV","sort":500000,"permission":{"default":0,"uZJKPuqDv0BBLk9c":3,"VnnpieLwbiAu3Owf":3,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e":{"initialization-folder":"Bestiary"},"wfrp4e-core":{"initialization-folder":"Bestiary","sort":400001}}}
{"_id":"Vz9Z85E8JmZFGiiq","name":"Schilderheim","content":"<ul>\n<li><strong>Tastes Like Chicken</strong>: Æpicarion — a wealthy merchant from Myrmiden in the Border Princes — has arrived in <strong>Schilderheim </strong>on his quest to eat one of every animal in the Old World. Now he has set his sights on the wildfowl of the region. The Schilderheim restaurateurs are more than happy to oblige, until, that is, people start disappearing. Townsfolk are certain Æpicarion is eating more than just wildfowl. Scared and desperate, they will hire any passing mercenaries to end the foreign merchant forever, or, at the very least, encourage him to move on. When such folk reach the Borderlander’s chamber, they will find Æpicarion dead, something having eaten its way out from inside his guts. Then the bodies start piling up, and the hired mercenaries are suddenly prime suspects; after all, who can be sure that it wasn’t them that killed Æpicarion?</li>\n</ul>","folder":"iltPBXW0kOqlZhfA","sort":1800001,"permission":{"default":2,"uZJKPuqDv0BBLk9c":3,"VnnpieLwbiAu3Owf":3,"hNHeJbKl47AOkoOO":3},"flags":{"wfrp4e":{"initialization-folder":"Settlements"},"wfrp4e-core":{"initialization-folder":"Settlements","sort":1800001}}}
